JOS – A gubernatorial aspirant under the platform of Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Plateau state, Honourable Timothy Golu, has Promised to restore true democratic governance on the Plateau if he becomes the next governor of Plateau state come 2023. According to Golu, a former member of the House of Representatives, what is basically lacking under the present administration on the Plateau is good governance. The former member representing Pankshin, Kanke Kanam federal constituency stated this when he paid a solidarity visit to his party’s executives at its secretariat in Jos. Pepco CEO Andy Bond To Step Down Due To Health Reasons Carabao Cup: Chelsea Ease Past Lacklustre Tottenham To Put One… He said, “True democratic governance stopped with the administration of David Jonah Jang, stressing that since the present administration took over in 2015 in the state, there is no more justice, there is no rule of law, as impunity becomes the order of the day,” Golu stressed. “That is what I am coming out to correct, I will return the state to the path of progress, equity and justice” Hon. Golu who also spoke on electoral reform, faulted President Muhammadu Buhari for refusing to sign the Electoral Act, saying President Buhari himself is a beneficiary of electoral reforms of the past administration.